.TH "ib_init_ah_attr_from_path" 9 "ib_init_ah_attr_from_path" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ib_init_ah_attr_from_path \- Initialize address handle attributes based on an SA path record.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ib_init_ah_attr_from_path
.BI "(struct ib_device *device "  ","
.BI "u8 port_num "  ","
.BI "struct sa_path_rec *rec "  ","
.BI "struct rdma_ah_attr *ah_attr "  ","
.BI "const struct ib_gid_attr *gid_attr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "device" 12
Device associated ah attributes initialization.
.IP "port_num" 12
Port on the specified device.
.IP "rec" 12
path record entry to use for ah attributes initialization.
.IP "ah_attr" 12
address handle attributes to initialization from path record.
.IP "gid_attr" 12
SGID attribute to consider during initialization.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
When \fBib_init_ah_attr_from_path\fP returns success,
(a) for IB link layer it optionally contains a reference to SGID attribute
when GRH is present for IB link layer.
(b) for RoCE link layer it contains a reference to SGID attribute.
User must invoke \fBrdma_destroy_ah_attr\fP to release reference to SGID
attributes which are initialized using \fBib_init_ah_attr_from_path\fP.
